                                <header>
                                    <h2 class="tm-blue-text tm-margin-b-45">Athletics</h2>
                                </header>

                                <p class="section-text">I have been a competitive athlete for as long as I can remember.
                                  I have played a large variety of sports, and forged friendships that will last a lifetime.
                                  I enjoy playing at a high level, because even though I play sports for fun, I enjoy
                                  pushing my limits in order to get better. Some of the sports that I play require teamwork,
                                  and others are individual sports. Both types are important to me because it is essential to
                                  be able to perform on your own, as well as in a team.<br><br>
                                </p>

                                <header>
                                    <h2 class="tm-blue-text tm-margin-b-45">Arts</h2>
                                </header>

                               <p class="section-text">I am also very fond of the arts. I love to play different instruments, as
                                 well as write for them. I play the Piano, the Banjo, the Guitar, and the Theremin. I find that
                                 playing music is a productive way to relax, as it still requires a high level of attention to detail,
                                 creativity, and dexterity.<br><br>
                                 Other than intrumental music, I have been performing in Musical Theatre productions since 2009.
                                 I began as an exclusive dancer, but broadened my horizons and took on singing parts as I progressed
                                 as a performer. The shows that I have been involved with have been the most important team experiences
                                 that I have had to date. There are so many different and eclectic personalities in theatre that must
                                 come together to put off a show, and every task involved cooperation and hard work. A good example of
                                 this is when it comes time to coordinate the cast with the orchestra. Teamwork is incredibly important
                                 as everyone on stage must have some sort of relationship with one another, and everyone is there to help each other.<br><br>
                               </p>
                             </section>

